The paper discusses the use of automated deduction and cognitive computing in deep question answering, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of information retrieval and machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the use of defeasible reasoning, which falls under the category of computational complexity and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper mentions the use of case-based reasoning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and the semantic structure of questions and answer candidates, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
